Main Responsibilities
1.	Quality System Construction 
o	Support the establishment of the rep office’s quality management system in alignment with ISO9001 requirements.
o	Manage and monitor key quality indicators and requirements to ensure effective implementation and continuous improvement.
2.	Audit & Certification Capability Platform 
o	Support the development of the rep office’s audit and certification capability platform.
o	Gain knowledge of and become familiar with ISO9001/14001/45001/22301/27001/27701 standards.
o	Assist the Director of the Quality Operations Department in capability development, including organizing audit and certification capability packages for each standard, summarizing best practices, and monitoring changes in external laws and regulations.
3.	Compliance & Regulatory Integration 
o	Support the systematic development of compliant operations and the internalization of external regulations within the rep office.
o	Understand and stay updated on EU laws and regulations.
o	Collaborate with the Country Compliance Officer to gain insights into external legal requirements.
o	Assist the Director of the Quality Operations Department in optimizing internal processes to ensure compliance within the rep office.
4.	Quality & Operations Assurance 
o	Assist the Director of the Rep Office and the Director of the Quality & Operations Department in completing essential quality and operations assurance tasks.
o	Responsibilities include contract and document management, facilitation of important document signing, and supporting key meeting arrangements.
